  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in West Virginia total $1B for FY2026 to date, with 3,333 awards and an average award size of $300K. Obligations are down 46.7% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Annual obligations peaked at $2B in FY24 and registered $1.9B in FY25, with earlier totals of $1.7B in FY23 and $1.5B in both FY22 and FY21. The top buying agencies so far are Department of Energy ($220M), Department of Justice ($184M), and Department of Veterans Affairs ($154M). Leading vendors by obligations include LEIDOS, INC. ($101M), IMPRES TECHNOLOGY SOLUTIONS, INC ($50.5M), and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION ($32.8M). The largest industry categories by obligations are Other Computer Related Services ($151M), Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) ($133M), and Engineering Services ($96.2M). This snapshot reflects fiscal-year-to-date activity and shows where federal spending has concentrated in the state so far this fiscal year.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What explains the year-over-year decline in obligations?",
        "body": "Obligations are down 46.7% year over year, with FY26 to date at $1B compared with prior fiscal-year totals as high as $2B in FY24 and $1.9B in FY25. The current-year total is partial (fiscal year to date), so FY26 to date reflects incomplete fiscal-year activity relative to full-year totals from prior years. Fiscal-year timing and the concentration of large awards in prior years are consistent with the observed reduction in obligations."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries dominate federal contracting in the state?",
        "body": "The top buying agencies for FY2026 to date are Department of Energy ($220M), Department of Justice ($184M), and Department of Veterans Affairs ($154M). The largest vendors are LEIDOS, INC. ($101M), IMPRES TECHNOLOGY SOLUTIONS, INC ($50.5M), and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION ($32.8M). Leading industry categories by obligations are Other Computer Related Services ($151M), Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) ($133M), and Engineering Services ($96.2M)."
      }
    ]
